				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Made Easy<a name="33072"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 5 04 10:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Now for the &quot;why you don't want to do it that way&quot; bit...
<br />

<br />
A single hotkey that sings more than one song can lead to death suddenly.  You cannot stop a macro/hotkey once it starts, it has to &quot;play out.&quot;
<br />

<br />
It's better to make 1 song per hotkey so that a missed note does not cause you problems.
<br />

<br />
/st
<br />
/cast #
<br />

<br />
That is all you need.  # is the gem number.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
