				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">You cannot stop a macro/hotkey once it starts, it has to &quot;play out.&quot; </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Not true... make a social hotbutton with one line in it:
<br />

<br />
/time
<br />

<br />
Hitting it will break any other macro in progress.  Thks Cujomatic.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  That said, I still think multi-song macros are more trouble than they're worth.  However, I do have a macro on my shaman to cast canni4 5 consecutive times with appropriate delays.  I use a /time macro to break it as needed, works like a charm.</span></td>
