				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Made Easy<a name="36256"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 23 04 8:49 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Besides missed notes, the reason I don't use hotkeys like this is because I find myself constantly switching the songs I'm twisting even during the course of a single battle.
<br />

<br />
For example, I might start with haste and an MR debuff or DOT at first, start twisting in mana song as the clerics start healing, or maybe the tank loses agro and so I have to mezz, or maybe I start twisting in snare &amp; chant as the mob starts to run away.
<br />

<br />
I guess what I'm saying is that the point of being a bard is versatility. I don't like being locked down into preset song combinations.
<br />

<br />
I agree with Shassiash's little mini-macro, though. I don't personally use them because the song-song doubletap helps me keep a rhythm, like a heartbeat, but to each her own.</span></td>
